  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Key Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age &gt;18 years.

          -  Able to provide informed consent.

          -  Has at least one de novo or restenotic lesion(s) with &gt; 70% stenosis documented
             angiographically of the SFA or popliteal artery. If more than one lesion requires
             intervention, only one should be treated as a study lesion.

        Key Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Has significant stenosis (&gt; 50%) or occlusion of inflow tract (proximal ipsilateral,
             iliofemoral, or aortic lesions) not successfully treated before this procedure.

          -  Lack of at least one patent runoff vessel with &lt; 50% stenosis throughout its course.

          -  Lesions in target area requiring atherectomy (or ablative devices), cutting balloons,
             cryoplasty balloons, or any other advanced device to facilitate angioplasty balloon or
             stent delivery.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
